Paul Osuyi, Asaba Gunmen have attacked members of a local vigilance group in Udu area of Delta State, killing two on the spot while a third is said to be receiving treatment at an undisclosed hospital for injuries. The vigilance members were said to be returning from a police station where they handed over criminal suspects when they were attacked by the hoodlums. Police public relations officer in the state, Onome Onovwakpoyeya, confirmed the incident yesterday in Asaba. 